if you build it is a 2013 documentary directed by patrick creadon , produced by neal baer , and filmed on location largely in the town of windsor and surrounding bertie county , north carolina , the state 's poorest county . the documentary follows a year in the life of an innovative , &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; high school program , culminating with the design and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; construction of a farmer 's market pavilion , the only farmers market pavilion in the u.s. designed and built by high school students . the film 's title is a truncated reference to the catchphrase " if you build it , they will come , " from the 1989 film , field of dreams .